Package org.ontal.imgutil.impl

Class AdjustedImage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ontal.imgutil.impl.AdjustedImage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OImage
    public class AdjustedImage
extends Object
implements OImage
    OImage implementation class oriented to process and transform image according to "adjust" processing strategy (Strategy.ADJUST) provided in the Settings parameter during the constructor call.

    The particular transformation algorithm consists in fitting and centering the uncut input image onto the targets canvas with its original ratio conserved leaving unocupied canvas space filled with provided background color. Useful when a user needs to standardize the output dimmensions and at the same time maintain the original image uncut.

    There is no Settings constructor provided with background color parameter, so user is encouraged to set it manually. If left unspecified the default beckground color is black.
    Since:
    May 2012
    Author:
    akaine
